1Ô∏è‚É£ Create a Model (Basic)

php artisan make:model User

app/Models/User.php

2Ô∏è‚É£ Model with Migration

php artisan make:model Post -m

app/Models/Post.php
database/migrations/xxxx_xx_xx_create_posts_table.php

3Ô∏è‚É£ Model with Controller + Migration
php artisan make:model Product -mc

app/Models/Product.php
app/Http/Controllers/ProductController.php
database/migrations/xxxx_xx_xx_create_products_table.php

4Ô∏è‚É£ Basic Model Structure

app/Models/Post.php

<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class Post extends Model
{
    protected $table = 'posts';   // optional if same name
    protected $fillable = ['title', 'content'];
}

PART 2Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî ACTIVE RECORD PATTERN

Model = Data + Database Logic

üîÅ With Active Record (Eloquent) 

$post = new Post();
$post->title = "Hello";
$post->content = "World";
$post->save();

1Ô∏è‚É£ Insert Data (Create)
Post::create([
    'title' => 'First Post',
    'content' => 'Laravel Active Record'
]);

2Ô∏è‚É£ Read Data (Select)

$posts = Post::all();          // SELECT * FROM posts
$post  = Post::find(1);       // SELECT WHERE id=1

3Ô∏è‚É£ Update Data

$post = Post::find(1);
$post->title = "Updated Title";
$post->save();

4Ô∏è‚É£ Delete Data

$post = Post::find(1);
$post->delete();

PART 3Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî ACTIVE RECORD IN CONTROLLER

app/Http/Controllers/PostController.php

use App\Models\Post;

class PostController extends Controller
{
    public function store()
    {
        Post::create([
            'title' => 'New Post',
            'content' => 'Active Record Example'
        ]);

        return "Post Saved";
    }

    public function index()
    {
        $posts = Post::all();
        return view('posts', compact('posts'));
    }
}

PART 4Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî ACTIVE RECORD RELATIONSHIPS
üîπ One to Many
class User extends Model
{
    public function posts()
    {
        return $this->hasMany(Post::class);
    }
}

$user = User::find(1);
$user->posts;
